content.description: Fun low angle climbing with a technical crux midways up. Wanders a bit around the bolt line. Mostly chert crimping but there are a few of the crystal pockets here and there up high when it gets tough again. Fun! The start is a little weird so consider sticking the first bolt if you’re unsure.
content.protection: 11 bolts to lower offs. Might need a 70.
content.location: Leftmost route on the big grey slab on the right side of the big corner of the Biscuit.

content.description:
A nice long, somewhat wandering route. Lots of chert crimping. A couple big sidepulls and jugs make for a fun crux about midways up. Higher on the route, it’s easier to travel a bit right of the bolt line on a vague aerie feature before moving left into a white rock scar with cool holds.

 There is a barn owl (Fall 2018) in the big hole to the right of this route. Don't be rude.
content.location: Rightmost route on the big grey slab on the right side of the big corner of the Biscuit. Just left of a low-angle chossy corner feature.

content.description: A big slab with tall continuously chertific routes.
